<p>
  {dgettext(
    "help_bots",
    "BotService lets you create and manage extensible bots that live in channels, respond to messages, greet users, and execute custom commands. Bots are built on a pluggable capability system — each bot can be configured with different behaviors."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_wrench}>{dgettext("help_bots", "Capabilities")}</.help_h4>
<p>{dgettext("help_bots", "Each bot can have one or more capabilities enabled:")}</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Mentions")}</strong> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— responds when someone mentions the bot by name"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Greeter")}</strong>
    {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— welcomes users when they join a channel, optionally says goodbye on part"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Custom Commands")}</strong>
    {dgettext("help_bots", "— user-defined")}
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!BotName trigger")}</code>
    {dgettext("help_bots", "commands with configurable responses")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Help")}</strong>
    {dgettext("help_bots", "— built-in")} <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!BotName help")}</code>
    {dgettext("help_bots", "command that lists available commands")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Dice")}</strong>
    {dgettext("help_bots", "— RPG dice rolling with standard notation (")}<code>2d6</code>, <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "d20+5")}</code>, <code>4d6kh3</code>{dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "). Use"
    )} <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!BotName roll <notation>")}</code>
    {dgettext("help_bots", "to roll dice")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Moderation")}</strong>
    {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— auto-moderation that monitors all messages for blocked words, spam, flood, and caps lock abuse. Configurable actions: warn, mute, or kick"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Trivia")}</strong> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— interactive quiz with 6 categories, scoring, and timers. Use"
    )}
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!BotName trivia start")}</code> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "to begin a round"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Scheduler")}</strong> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— posts scheduled/periodic messages to channels. Supports interval (every N minutes) and daily (at HH:MM UTC) schedules"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "RSS")}</strong> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— monitors RSS/Atom feeds and posts new items to channels. Use"
    )}
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!BotName rss add <url> <#channel>")}</code> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "to add a feed"
    )}
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  {dgettext(
    "help_bots",
    "Additional capabilities (LLM, Script, Game) are planned for future releases."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_tab_control}>{dgettext("help_bots", "How Bots Work")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {dgettext(
    "help_bots",
    "Each bot runs as its own process on the server. When a message arrives in a channel the bot has joined, the bot checks each capability in order. Passive capabilities (like Moderation) run on every message, while active capabilities use first-match-wins. A cooldown timer prevents the bot from responding too frequently."
  )}
</p>
<p>
  {dgettext("help_bots", "Bots appear in the channel nicklist with a")} <strong>⚙</strong>
  {dgettext(
    "help_bots",
    "prefix and are grouped below regular users. They can be kicked or banned from channels like normal users."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_shield}>{dgettext("help_bots", "Permissions")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {dgettext("help_bots", "Only")} <strong>admins</strong>
  and <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "server operators")}</strong>
  {dgettext(
    "help_bots",
    "can create, modify, or delete bots. All users can view bot info and use bot commands."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_dice}>{dgettext("help_bots", "Dice Notation")}</.help_h4>
<p>{dgettext("help_bots", "The Dice capability supports standard RPG notation:")}</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "NdS")}</code> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— roll N dice with S sides (e.g.,"
    )} <code>2d6</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "dS")}</code> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— shorthand for 1 die (e.g.,"
    )} <code>d20</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "NdS+M")}</code> {dgettext("help_bots", "— add modifier (e.g.,")} <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "d20+5")}</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "NdS-M")}</code> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— subtract modifier (e.g.,"
    )} <code>d8-2</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "NdSkhK")}</code> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— keep highest K dice (e.g.,"
    )} <code>4d6kh3</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "NdSklK")}</code> {dgettext(
      "help_bots",
      "— keep lowest K dice (e.g.,"
    )} <code>2d20kl1</code>)
  </li>
</ul>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_question}>{dgettext("help_bots", "Trivia Categories")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {dgettext(
    "help_bots",
    "Available trivia categories: general, science, history, geography, technology, entertainment."
  )}
</p>
<p>
  {dgettext("help_bots", "Commands:")} <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!Bot trivia start")}</code>, <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!Bot trivia stop")}</code>, <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!Bot trivia score")}</code>,
  <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "!Bot answer <text>")}</code>
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_code}>{dgettext("help_bots", "Template Placeholders")}</.help_h4>
<p>{dgettext("help_bots", "Bot responses support these placeholders:")}</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <code>{"{nickname}"}</code> {dgettext("help_bots", "— the user who triggered the response")}
  </li>
  <li><code>{"{channel}"}</code> {dgettext("help_bots", "— the current channel name")}</li>
  <li><code>{"{topic}"}</code> {dgettext("help_bots", "— the current channel topic")}</li>
  <li>
    <code>{"{prefix}"}</code> {dgettext("help_bots", "— the bot's command prefix (e.g.,")} <code>!</code>)
  </li>
  <li><code>{"{botname}"}</code> {dgettext("help_bots", "— the bot's display name")}</li>
</ul>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_laptop}>{dgettext("help_bots", "Management Dialog")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {dgettext("help_bots", "Open the Bot Management dialog from the")}
  <strong>{dgettext("help_bots", "Tools")}</strong>
  {dgettext("help_bots", "menu or by typing")} <code>{dgettext("help_bots", "/bot")}</code>
  {dgettext(
    "help_bots",
    "with no arguments (admin only). The dialog shows all bots with a split-view: select a bot on the left to see its details, channels, commands, and event hooks on the right."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_link}>{dgettext("help_bots", "See Also")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  <.help_link topic="bot-command">{dgettext("help_bots", "/bot Command Reference")}</.help_link>
  ·
  <.help_link topic="bot-custom-commands">
    {dgettext("help_bots", "Bot Custom Commands")}
  </.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-dice">{dgettext("help_bots", "Dice")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-trivia">{dgettext("help_bots", "Trivia")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-scheduler">{dgettext("help_bots", "Scheduler")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-rss">{dgettext("help_bots", "RSS")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-moderation">{dgettext("help_bots", "Moderation")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="chanserv">{dgettext("help_bots", "ChanServ")}</.help_link>
</p>
